2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper considers both time-dependent and state-dependent graphs, which are commonly studied in the context of social and information networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses convergence properties of consensus algorithms, which is a topic of interest in control theory and systems engineering. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper involves iterative updates of node states, which is a common technique in machine learning algorithms. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with consensus algorithms in a multiagent setting, which is the focus of this sub-category.
